WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.000
Tour of London

00:05.440 --> 00:08.280
Welcome to this short tour of London

00:09.080 --> 00:14.640
This square is Trafalgar Square and it is the middle of London

00:15.640 --> 00:23.400
We're standing opposite the National Gallery a famous museum with lots of famous paintings

00:24.400 --> 00:29.560
From here we'll walk along the Red Street to Buckingham Palace

00:30.240 --> 00:32.240
The Queen lives there

00:33.200 --> 00:37.960
Turn left and go to the houses of Parliament and Big Ben

00:39.480 --> 00:42.440
Opposite you can see the London Eye

00:43.560 --> 00:45.560
It takes you

00:46.120 --> 00:48.680
135 meters above the River Thames

00:49.480 --> 00:52.400
You can see most of London on a clear day

00:53.880 --> 00:58.680
When you are tired the best way to see London is by boat

00:59.440 --> 01:02.080
You can get the boat near Big Ben

01:02.960 --> 01:07.520
As you go along the river the London Eye is on your right

01:08.880 --> 01:11.680
Get off the boat at Tower Bridge

01:12.640 --> 01:15.960
Next to the bridge is the Tower of London

01:16.480 --> 01:19.320
It's over 900 years old

01:20.320 --> 01:27.560
After visiting the Tower of London take the boat back along the river to the railway station

01:28.560 --> 01:34.000
When you get off the boat go past the station and walk along the street

01:35.200 --> 01:40.240
Turn left into King Street and go past a church

01:41.440 --> 01:47.760
You're now back at the square and this is where we'll finish our tour

